abstract: A new report sent to Congress about the drone strike that killed Iran’s top general contradicted the original justification the administration provided.
snippet: A new report sent to Congress about the drone strike that killed Iran’s top general contradicted the original justification the administration provided.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The White House told Congress on Friday that President Trump authorized the strike last month that killed Iran’s most important general to respond to attacks that had already taken place and deter future ones, contradicting the president’s claim that he acted in response to an imminent threat.

abstract: The public struggles of White House adviser Kellyanne Conway and her husband, George T. Conway III, are not shtick, friends say, and they are not having fun.
snippet: The public struggles of White House adviser Kellyanne Conway and her husband, George T. Conway III, are not shtick, friends say, and they are not having fun.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — George T. Conway III has described the work of his wife, Kellyanne Conway, for President Trump in terms usually reserved for hostage situations: brainwashed by a cult, suffering from Stockholm syndrome, an overwhelmed mother protecting a destructive man-child.

abstract: Agents from a special tactical team that normally confronts smugglers on the border are being sent to sanctuary cities across the country.
snippet: Agents from a special tactical team that normally confronts smugglers on the border are being sent to sanctuary cities across the country.
lead_paragraph: The Trump administration is deploying law enforcement tactical units from the southern border as part of a supercharged arrest operation in sanctuary cities across the country, an escalation in the president’s battle against localities that refuse to participate in immigration enforcement.

abstract: Amid turmoil in the U.S. attorney’s office in Washington, the attorney general has also sent outside prosecutors to review other politically sensitive cases.
snippet: Amid turmoil in the U.S. attorney’s office in Washington, the attorney general has also sent outside prosecutors to review other politically sensitive cases.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Attorney General William P. Barr has assigned an outside prosecutor to scrutinize the criminal case against President Trump’s former national security adviser Michael T. Flynn, according to people familiar with the matter.

abstract: The decision to decline charges appears to be a move to distance the Justice Department from President Trump, who has long attacked Mr. McCabe.
snippet: The decision to decline charges appears to be a move to distance the Justice Department from President Trump, who has long attacked Mr. McCabe.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Andrew G. McCabe, the former deputy F.B.I. director and a frequent target of President Trump’s, will not face charges in an investigation into whether he lied to investigators about a media leak, his defense team said on Friday.

abstract: American negotiators had insisted on a decline in hostilities — though not a complete cease-fire — before signing an agreement with the Taliban.
snippet: American negotiators had insisted on a decline in hostilities — though not a complete cease-fire — before signing an agreement with the Taliban.
lead_paragraph: MUNICH — American officials said on Friday they had agreed with the Taliban on a seven-day reduction in violence in Afghanistan that, if it holds, would be followed by an Afghan peace agreement after 18 years of war.

abstract: Russian troops are engaging in standoffs with U.S. troops guarding oil fields and fighting remnants of the Islamic State.
snippet: Russian troops are engaging in standoffs with U.S. troops guarding oil fields and fighting remnants of the Islamic State.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Russia is intensifying a pressure campaign on U.S. military forces in northeastern Syria following the American withdrawal from much of that area ahead of a Turkish cross-border offensive last fall, American military and diplomatic officials say.

abstract: A whipsaw week of charged decisions by the Justice Department, some favored by the president and others not, has bewildered much of Washington.
snippet: A whipsaw week of charged decisions by the Justice Department, some favored by the president and others not, has bewildered much of Washington.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — When President Trump learned that the Justice Department was dropping a case against a former F.B.I. official whom he considered one of his longtime enemies, his immediate response was anger. As he flipped on the television Friday and watched how the story was being covered, that anger only mounted.
